reviews.text: My wife and I ate here for dinner. The only reason for the 4 star rating was that our waitress was not really in any hurry to take care of us. Out side of that the wings were extremely good. We got a meal that came with a pitcher of iced tea, a huge and I mean huge basket of fries, and 20 wings. Very reasonably priced and the wings are so worth it. We will be coming back the next time we are in Buffalo for sure

Pick up a bottle of Duffs sauce for the house and as a gift to send to your friends far away, it's great, especially on the BBQ grille.  I usually only order the fried shrimp basket, but there's no denying that the wings are great and hot. There's a lot more to the menu than just chicken wings just so you know. You'll leave completely stuffed and happy! Take out orders are almost always ready within 10 to 15 minutes.

This place was great. We ordered the special with  20 wings, a large fries, and a large pitcher of soda for $35.00. So much food. We couldn't eat all of it! We got the medium sauce....just spicy enough for us. A definite place we will come back to if we are in the Buffalo NY area

It feels very much like a chain. We walked in while a grade school sports team was there with their parents which affected the atmosphere. Really tasty wings. The double char—something or other, ask about this, was really fantastic. But the spice just wasn’t there on their hottest wings. They advertise over and over, in your face, how dangerous the heat of their wings is. And it’s just not at the level you want it to be if you’re looking for real heat. Staff was nice, and I’d return if I was nearby and craving wings. Although, I’d definitely want to check out more spots nearby first.

Legendary, amazing, always delicious!!! My wife who grew up in East NY cannot believe how awesome the wings are here, anytime we're in the area we make sure to stop at least one time! The service is always super fast and everyone is always friendly!!! We can't wait till we're out this way again to come back!! Or.   You could just open a location out here in the Albany area!!!

Food was very tasty and well done. Server was excellent at ensuring our celiac dinner had only gluten free food. Good specials and we all left very full. Any of the curry's good choices and the crispy tofu is excellent.

The food was great and the atmosphere was very relaxed. I recommend this place to anyone but know what you're ordering!! Ask questions! Or better yet, look through their little black book with pictures of every dish they offer!

Holy delicious food, Batman. Had dinner here with Tea, Coconut Rice, Ginger Beef, Lemongrass Chicken, and Black Bean Vegetables. Servers were prompt and extremely nice to talk to. My Dad and his Wife had a Soup Appetizer, they really enjoyed. Even the water had cucumbers and mint in it. 

Make sure you don't park in the Circle K parking lot, because you can be at risk of getting a $100 ticket. This is very clearly posted in the restaurant. Underground parking is available. 

Deserts looked wonderful, but we were too full to try them.

A good restaurant but as other reviews has stated it caters more to Western tastes rather then authentic Thai food. Which is evident by the picture book accompanying the menu. 

The poppy shrimp are very good they come with this curried mayo that is pretty good.

The restaurant itself is clean, the service is attentive and they always came around asking how we were doing. 

Overall it's a good restaurant that would be a good first venture for somebody looking to try Thai food.

This is the best Thai food in Edmonton， their curry tastes super good.  Their food are fresh and clean. The environment is great and the staffs are really really nice.  The wait time is short， their dishes comes out fast. This is my number one recommendation for Thai food in Edmonton.

One of the best restaurants in town. By far the best selection of fresh sushi. They have a few hours they do not sell it. They deliver too with Mr. Delivery. The food is always hot fast and fresh. There is times where a reservation may be needed. They get quite busy on Friday and Saturday nights.
Our waitress was very nice and helped us with any questions we had. Nice quiet environment. The food was good!
Great food. We got a meal for two (fine two of us) and there was way too much food. Would recommend an ordering ratio of two meals per three or four people.

The food was excellent. We came in on a very snowy night, so the warm and delicious food was very welcome! The restaurant is a good size and the menu looked very good and authentic Korean. The braised short ribs (gal-bi) were especially delicious. The spicy isn't very spicy, but was still delicious. We didn't try the barbeque, but others around us did and it smelled amazing. We plan to come back and give that a try as well!

Excellent!  My wife and I had lunch here with our boys.  This was my wife’s first time eating Korean food and our server was extremely helpful.  The food was as good as the service.  Highly recommended.
